        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer134358246" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2781763230446118204">This may have been the first YA &quot;dystopia&quot; I ever read. The genre has gone through many changes since then but this book continues to stick in my mind as one which cemented my love for it. It&apos;s an old tale of forbidden romance but avoids being cheesy. It&apos;s a tale of heartache and tragedy but steers clear of melodrama. One thing is certain: Sephy and Callum&apos;s story will stay with me for a long time.</span>
  <span id="freeText2781763230446118204" style="display:none">This may have been the first YA "dystopia" I ever read. The genre has gone through many changes since then but this book continues to stick in my mind as one which cemented my love for it. It's an old tale of forbidden romance but avoids being cheesy. It's a tale of heartache and tragedy but steers clear of melodrama. One thing is certain: Sephy and Callum's story will stay with me for a long time.</span>
