<div id="review_2562077716" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2562077716" />
    <a title="Ken" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/38999260-ken"><img alt="Ken" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1446483502p2/38999260.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2562077716?book_show_action=true">Oct 16, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ken" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ken" href="/user/show/38999260-ken">Ken</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/32489974-noughts-crosses">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2562077716" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5539736906080753236">After Blackman was announced as one of the writers on the new series of Doctor Who, I really wanted to read one of her novels so that I could get a feel for her work.<br/>As her episode is going to focus on Rosa Parker’s and the constant theme of this book was race and segregation, I ended up getting even more of a gasp on what her episode might be like than I originally expected.<br/>This book was just so incredible!<br/><br/>Set in an alternate universe where dark skinned people known as crosses are the superior </span>
  <span id="freeText5539736906080753236" style="display:none">After Blackman was announced as one of the writers on the new series of Doctor Who, I really wanted to read one of her novels so that I could get a feel for her work.<br />As her episode is going to focus on Rosa Parker’s and the constant theme of this book was race and segregation, I ended up getting even more of a gasp on what her episode might be like than I originally expected.<br />This book was just so incredible!<br /><br />Set in an alternate universe where dark skinned people known as crosses are the superior race.<br />The story follows teenagers Sephy (a Cross) and Callum (a Nought) who struggle to understand why they have to be segregated.<br /><br />The story narrative switches between the two perspectives as both make sense of the world they live in, I found the scene were Callum is questioning why there’s no references to any noughts in the school curriculum just so powerful.<br /><br />I really liked both characters and was really rooting for it to work out for them, with so much adversity I was completely wrapped up and shocked with how the final third played out.<br />I was completely hooked!<br /><br />I’m really excited to see Blackman’s take on Doctor Who, I’m glad the show has brought her to my attention. <br />I really want to read the next book as soon as possible!</span>
  <a data-text-id="5539736906080753236" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


